  "body": "according to https://eth.wiki/json-rpc/API#hex-value-encoding\r\nValue representing unformatted data like byte arrays, account addresses, hashes, bytecode arrays, must \"encode as hex, prefix with “0x”, two hex digits per byte\"\r\n\r\nhardhat return \"0x0\" for `eth_getStorageAt` for empty data while it should return `0x`\r\n\r\nThe issue might be present for other rpc call ?\r\n\r\nWhile client library can potentially handle it, it would be better for hardhat to be fully json rpc compliant (https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/issues/1132)\r\n",
